_exec_summary.SummaryText:
 Chemicals conducted a comprehensive review of the covered system, as well as administrative, technical, operating and maintenance procedures in addition to the other required program elements of the Rule.  This review concluded that ChemQuest Chemicals meets the requirements of the RMP Rule, 40 CFR 68.  In an effort to continuously improve the overall health, safety and environment (HSE) at the facility, ChemQuest Chemicals has scheduled the following actions:

     ?    Install area NH3 sensors (Complete by August 3rd,2016);

     ?    Install electric alarm system that can be heard throughout the plant (Complete by August 3rd,2016);

     ?    Install normally closed pneumatic valves on the 29% storage tank (Complete by August 3rd,2016);

     ?    Install a low level alarm in the scrubber (Complete by August 3rd, 2016);

     ?    Install isolation valves on all system gauges (Complete by August 3rd, 2016);

     ?    Tank integrity testing by a qualified professional (Complete by August 3rd, 2016); and

     ?    Weather monitoring procedure (Complete by June 3rd, 2016).



At a minimum the RMP will be audited at least every three years and updated and renewed every five years.  Any necessary changes to the to the ERP or any other relevant programs or procedures would be made on an ongoing and as needed basis or following an incident investigation, RMP audit or RMP renewal.
